21// An accessor must have a getter, but can have no setter.
22//
23// When setting a property, V8 searches accessors in prototypes.
24// If an accessor was found and it does not have a setter,
25// the request is ignored.
26//
27// If the accessor in the prototype has the READ_ONLY property attribute, then
28// a new value is added to the derived object when the property is set.
29// This shadows the accessor in the prototype.
30class AccessorInfo
31 : public TorqueGeneratedAccessorInfo<AccessorInfo, HeapObject> {
32 public:
33 // This is a wrapper around |maybe_redirected_getter| accessor which
34 // returns/accepts C function and converts the value from and to redirected
35 // pointer.
36 DECL_EXTERNAL_POINTER_ACCESSORS_MAYBE_READ_ONLY_HOST(getter, Address)
37 inline void init_getter_redirection(IsolateForSandbox isolate);
38 inline void remove_getter_redirection(IsolateForSandbox isolate);
39 inline bool has_getter(Isolate* isolate);
40
41 // The field contains the address of the C function.
42 DECL_EXTERNAL_POINTER_ACCESSORS_MAYBE_READ_ONLY_HOST(setter, Address)
43 inline bool has_setter(Isolate* isolate);
44
45 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(is_special_data_property)
46 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(replace_on_access)
47 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(is_sloppy)
48
49 inline SideEffectType getter_side_effect_type() const;
50 inline void set_getter_side_effect_type(SideEffectType type);
51
52 inline SideEffectType setter_side_effect_type() const;
53 inline void set_setter_side_effect_type(SideEffectType type);
54
55 // The property attributes used when an API object template is instantiated
56 // for the first time. Changing of this value afterwards does not affect
57 // the actual attributes of a property.
58 inline PropertyAttributes initial_property_attributes() const;
59 inline void set_initial_property_attributes(PropertyAttributes attributes);
60
61 // Checks whether the given receiver is compatible with this accessor.
62 static bool IsCompatibleReceiverMap(Handle<AccessorInfo> info,
63 Handle<Map> map);
64 inline bool IsCompatibleReceiver(Tagged<Object> receiver);
65
66 // Append all descriptors to the array that are not already there.
67 // Return number added.
68 static int AppendUnique(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> descriptors,
69 Handle<FixedArray> array, int valid_descriptors);
70
71 DECL_PRINTER(AccessorInfo)
72
73 inline void clear_padding();
74
75 class BodyDescriptor;
76
77 private:
78 // When simulator is enabled the field stores the "redirected" address of the
79 // C function (the one that's callabled from simulated compiled code), in
80 // this case the original address of the C function has to be taken from the
81 // redirection.
82 // For native builds the field contains the address of the C function.
83 // This field is initialized implicitly via respective |getter|-related
84 // methods.
85 DECL_EXTERNAL_POINTER_ACCESSORS(maybe_redirected_getter, Address)
86
87 // Bit positions in |flags|.
88 DEFINE_TORQUE_GENERATED_ACCESSOR_INFO_FLAGS()
89
90 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(AccessorInfo)
91};
92

96 static Tagged<AccessCheckInfo> Get(Isolate* isolate,
97 Handle<JSObject> receiver);
98
99 using BodyDescriptor = StructBodyDescriptor;
100
101 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(AccessCheckInfo)

104class InterceptorInfo
105 : public TorqueGeneratedInterceptorInfo<InterceptorInfo, Struct> {
106 public:
107 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(can_intercept_symbols)
108 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(non_masking)
109 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(is_named)
110 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(has_no_side_effect)
111 // TODO(ishell): remove support for old signatures once they go through
112 // Api deprecation process.

114
115 DEFINE_TORQUE_GENERATED_INTERCEPTOR_INFO_FLAGS()
116
117 using BodyDescriptor = StructBodyDescriptor;
118
119 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(InterceptorInfo)
120};
